                    <span class="legend-top">Top surface</span>
                    <span class="legend-shock">Attached shock</span>
                    <span class="legend-leading">Leading edge</span>
                  </div>
                  <p id="waverider-summary">Generated 3D waverider geometry.</p>
                </div>
                <figure id="fallback-figure" class="inlet-figure result-figure" hidden>
                  <img id="fallback-plot" src="" alt="Fallback ICC, FCT, and evolute curves" />
                  <figcaption>Improper input fallback: FCT, ICC, and clipped evolute curves.</figcaption>
                </figure>
                <pre id="waverider-log" class="waverider-log"></pre>
              </div>
            </section>

            <section class="cma-panel">
              <div>
                <h3>CMA-ES Optimization</h3>
                <p>Actual CMA-ES output generated from the initial waverider inputs.</p>
              </div>
              <figure class="static-cma-figure" aria-label="Static CMA-ES before and after curve plot">
                <img src="/hypersonic-cma-icc-before-after.png" alt="Actual CMA-ES ICC before and after output plotted against FCT" />
                <figcaption>Initial inputs: Mach 4, gamma 1.4, shock beta 20 deg, seed points 101, ghost points 5, span 0.5 m, CMA control points 9, FCT Cosine [-0.1, 4, 0, -0.11, 1], ICC Cosine [0.01, 4, 0, 0, 1]. CMA-ES run: 80 generations, popsize 32.</figcaption>
              </figure>
            </section>

            <div class="code-walkthrough">
              <div class="code-intro">
                <h3>CMA-ES and Evolute Injectivity Metric</h3>
                <p>The optimizer edits ICC control points, scores each candidate with an evolute-injectivity penalty, and sends the final centered curve back into the browser plotter.</p>
              </div>
              {cmaCodeSections.map((section) => (
                <section class="code-section">
                  <h3>{section.title}</h3>
                  <p>{section.explanation}</p>
                  <pre><code>{section.code}</code></pre>
                </section>
              ))}
            </div>

            <section class="inlet-live-panel">
              <div>
                <h3>Live Inlet Geometry</h3>
                <p>Run the inlet sweep with editable geometry inputs and refresh the TPR, throat, and target geometry plots.</p>
              </div>
              <button type="button" id="run-inlet-matlab" class="secondary-action">Run Inlet Sweep</button>
              <form id="inlet-form" class="inlet-form">
                <label><span>Mach</span><input name="mach" type="number" step="0.1" value="4" /></label>
                <label><span>Gamma</span><input name="gamma" type="number" step="0.01" value="1.4" /></label>
                <label><span>Ramps</span><input name="n_ramps" type="number" step="1" value="3" /></label>
                <label><span>Yc</span><input name="y_c" type="number" step="0.01" value="0.33" /></label>
                <label><span>Target throat</span><input name="target_throat" type="number" step="0.005" value="0.05" /></label>
                <label><span>X count</span><input name="num_x" type="number" step="1" value="1" /></label>
                <label><span>X min</span><input name="x_min" type="number" step="0.05" value="0.5" /></label>
                <label><span>X max</span><input name="x_max" type="number" step="0.05" value="1.3" /></label>
                <label><span>Beta count</span><input name="num_beta" type="number" step="1" value="50" /></label>
                <label><span>Beta min</span><input name="beta_min_deg" type="number" step="0.1" value="14.58" /></label>
